    },
    {
      "term": "reversible_runs_free",
      "reading": "the exoneration clause, the half everyone forgets: dissipation is not a tax on computation, it is a tax on erasure alone. a move licensed by the readings — one that merges nothing — writes nothing to the transcript: run it at every step for as long as you like and the record cannot tell you did. the gauge sector runs free, and that is why the bill, when it arrives, is attributable to the merge and to nothing else. computation was never the expensive part",
